Use Cases:

Class :     Collections of objects like methods, variables.
Object:     Instance of a Class.
Packages:   Packages are used to store the relative files together.
Interface:  Interface is used to define key methods, and variables.

OOPs

    WHO ?                     WHAT ?                                                           WHY ?

1. Inheritance:     acquiring properties of its parent Class.                           CODE RE-USEABILITY
2. Polymorphism:    one task is performed in different ways.                            FLEXIBILITY
                    (method overloading and method overriding)
3. Abstraction:     Hiding internal details and showing functionality                   SECURITY
4. Encapsulation:   Binding (or wrapping) code and data together into a single unit
                    (eg. Classes, methods, labels, package etc.)                        SECURITY